<subSubSection id="879865625C561649F9FFF827FD13F868" pageId="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF3D36E95C561649F9FFF827FD13F868" blockId="5.[151,1436,1940,2037]" pageId="5">
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C561649F9FFF827FEC0F831" bold="true" box="[151,273,1940,1965]" pageId="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species has an almost completely carinate propodeum with a well-defined area superomedia and very strongly tapered mandibles that are apically twisted, so when they are closed they appear more or less unidentate and needle-sharp (
<bibRefCitation id="AB134B185C561649F888F86FFD66F868" author="Gauld" box="[480,695,2012,2037]" pageId="5" refString="Gauld, I., Sithole, R., Gomes, J. U. &amp; Godoy, C. (2002) The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica, 4. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 66, 1 - 768." type="journal article" year="2002">
Gauld, 
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C561649FB5CF86EFDB4F869" box="[564,613,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="5">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number id="794A24CE5C561649FB12F86FFD66F868" box="[634,695,2012,2036]" pageId="5" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="879865625C55164AF9AFFF24FE75FEDC" pageId="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CF3D36E95C55164AF9AFFF24FE75FEDC" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C55164AF9AFFF24FEEAFF2C" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AB134B185C55164AF82BFF24FDD9FF2C" author="Gauld" box="[323,520,151,176]" pageId="6" refString="Gauld, I., Sithole, R., Gomes, J. U. &amp; Godoy, C. (2002) The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica, 4. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 66, 1 - 768." type="journal article" year="2002">
Gauld 
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C55164AF8E7FF2AFE18FF2C" box="[399,457,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="794A24CE5C55164AF8B8FF2BFDD9FF2C" box="[464,520,152,176]" pageId="6" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
reported considerable variation in color in this species, however we did not find such variation in the color pattern of the species when comparing our material with the 
<typeStatus id="1039884B5C55164AFD02FF0EFB07FF49" box="[1130,1238,189,213]" pageId="6">paratypes</typeStatus>
at the 
<collectionCode id="A993AE2C5C55164AFC49FF0EFAA8FF48" box="[1313,1401,189,212]" pageId="6">BMNH</collectionCode>
. 
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C55164AF9AFFF6CFEB1FF64" bold="true" box="[199,352,223,248]" pageId="6">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="B79576795C55164AF803FF53FE3AFF64" box="[363,491,223,248]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="6">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B79576795C55164AF893FF6CFD92FF64" box="[507,579,223,248]" name="Brazil" pageId="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The specimens were collected in Brazilian savannah (Itapeva Ecological Station) and semideciduous forest (Mogi Guaçu Ecological Station), in São Paulo State, Southeast 
<collectingCountry id="B79576795C55164AFD81FEB7FAE0FE81" box="[1257,1329,260,285]" name="Brazil" pageId="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis id="FDF6EAFB5C55164AF9AFFE94FEF6FEDC" bold="true" box="[199,295,295,320]" pageId="6">Biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
